'''West Lancashire''' is a [[non-metropolitan district]] with the [[borough status in the United Kingdom|status of a borough]] in Lancashire, England. Its council is based in [[Ormskirk]]. The other town in the borough is [[Skelmersdale]].

The district was formed in 1974 under the [[Local Government Act 1972]], as a merger of [[Ormskirk Urban District|Ormskirk]] and [[Skelmersdale and Holland]] [[Urban district (Great Britain and Ireland)|urban district]]s along with part of [[West Lancashire Rural District]] and part of the former [[Wigan Rural District]].

